Ever since I made the decision to go to @moeandco.black I have felt soo welcommed and have been treated like a part of their family. 
I know for some men going to the barbers can make them feel intimidated, anxious or generally it’s just something they don’t look forward to.
At @moeandco.black they are always so friendly, the wait times are short, I’m offered complimentary cold drinks, given great hair advice if I ask for it and of course I always walk away with the exact hair cut I wanted. It’s so lovely watching how great they are with young kids who are getting their first hair cuts and welcoming all ages to come in and walk out feeling amazing. 
I actually met the owner @mitchdimech the first time I went to @moeandco.black and after chatting about our bubs we realised they were born only 1 day apart in the same hospital and only rooms away. Two very proud dads 

Thank you for creating such a great environment

An amazing photo that reminds me how truely blessed we are as a family

My Grandfather Charlie lived and endured the horrors of WW2 in Hungary. He was only 3 years of age when the war broke out in 1939. He spent the war with his Mother and Siblings and experienced the rise and fall of Hungary. His Father fought in WW1 and then again in WW2. The family constantly wondered whether he was still alive or if they would ever see him again. The family dealt with Enemy soldiers constantly entering there home and taking there food. Which created desperation for Charlie and his family to go searching amidst the unknown dangers in the streets. What ever they had to do to survive.

By 1947 Charlie ended up suffering severe starvation and was sent away to a Family in Denmark by the Red Cross. He spent 12 months there before returning back to Hungary.

After the War he was forced to Enlist in the Army and was put to work in the Mines. Eventually he got the opportunity to seek Refuge overseas so he decided to leave and start a new life in Australia.

Currently 15/10/2023 he lays in his bed with his Great Grandson and helps feed him his bottle of milk 

Life is beautiful
